19/01/2004
VIENNA, Austria -- Three investigative journalists from the Balkans were awarded prizes by the Austrian chapter of Reporters Without Borders on Friday (16 January). Serbia's Jelena Bjelica received 5,000 euros for reporting on the trafficking of prostitutes in Kosovo. Another Serbian journalist, B92's Milorad Vesic, was recognised for uncovering corruption. Zeljko Peratovic of Croatia was honoured for reporting on war crimes in his country and how war criminals have profited from their abuses. (AFP - 16/01/04)
